Pesticide Action Network (PAN) was founded in 1982 and is a network of over 600 non-governmental organisations, institutions and individuals in over 60 countries worldwide working to minimise the negative effects and replace the use of harmful pesticides with ecologically sound alternatives. Its projects and campaigns are coordinated by five autonomous Regional Centres. &#xd;
&#xd;
PAN Europe is an active member of Health and environment Alliance (HEAL) and of European Environment Bureau (EEB)
